  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [x] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (a1f41be 2023-03-14T00:15:36.156534Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n forge init\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\n[Following Creating a New Project documentation](https://book.getfoundry.sh/projects/creating-a-new-project), when running `forge init forge` I get the following error:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nforge init forge\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nInitializing /Users/moo/code/executor/ethdubai-2023-hackathon/forge...\r\nInstalling forge-std in \"/Users/moo/code/executor/ethdubai-2023-hackathon/forge/lib/forge-std\" (url: Some(\"https://github.com/foundry-rs/forge-std\"), tag: None)\r\nError: \r\nfatal: pathspec '.gitmodules' did not match any files\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Existing git repository\r\n- macOS\r\n- zsh\r\n",
