    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I was having this exact issue when trying to use Foundry on a project that was already initialized to use git\r\n\r\nI did the test to initialize a new foundry project on both, **a total clean empty folder**, and **under a folder that has already been initialized with git**\r\n\r\nThe result, **in the clean empty folder**, the `forge init --force` command **works as a charm**, and **in the other project I was getting the .git error reported on this thread**, the solution to **works with Foundry under a project that has already been initialized with git it is to always add** the `--no-git` **option at the end of each** `forge install` command. i.e.\r\n```\r\nforge init --force --no-git\r\nforge install OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts --no-git\r\n```",
